headline: Is British American Tobacco a Buy, Sell, or Hold in 2025?
summary: If you're a dividend investor, you've likely considered buying British American Tobacco (NYSE: BTI), if you don't own it already.  British American Tobacco offers an appealing dividend yield of 7.9%, and it has the safety of a recession-proof business, as tobacco sales are generally unaffected by the broader conditions in the economy.  While British American Tobacco is up this year, it's been flat over the last five years.

headline: Asian Manufacturing PMIs Send Positive Signals But Tariff Threat Tempers Upside
summary: Manufacturing conditions across much of Asia looked slightly stronger midway through the fourth quarter, but trepidation about U.S. tariffs and the economic hit they’ll deal is taking some of the shine off the data.
